00:26:42,391 --> 00:26:46,933
remains never used.

654
00:26:46,968 --> 00:26:51,475
The park's ferris wheel

655
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:53,077
accumulates rust

656
00:26:53,078 --> 00:27:09,464
rather than riders.

657
00:27:09,465 --> 00:27:11,167
The bumper cars sit in a state

658
00:27:11,168 --> 00:27:19,046
of motionless decay.

659
00:27:19,081 --> 00:27:20,853
Pripyat has provided an amazing

660
00:27:20,888 --> 00:27:22,087
and rare opportunity

661
00:27:22,122 --> 00:27:23,286
to see what happens

662
00:27:23,287 --> 00:27:24,925
to a manmade city

663
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:32,572
when humans disappear.

664
00:27:32,573 --> 00:27:33,043
I can see

665
00:27:33,044 --> 00:27:34,210
from my Geiger counter

666
00:27:34,245 --> 00:27:35,407
that it's really quite safe

667
00:27:35,408 --> 00:27:36,374
to be here,

668
00:27:36,409 --> 00:27:38,482
radiation levels

669
00:27:38,517 --> 00:27:40,555
were not very high.

670
00:27:40,556 --> 00:27:41,523
but you can see

671
00:27:41,558 --> 00:27:42,724
that we've really hit

672
00:27:42,759 --> 00:27:43,890
a point of no return

673
00:27:43,891 --> 00:27:51,474
in recapturing these facilities.

674
00:27:51,509 --> 00:27:52,958
We're in what was

675
00:27:52,993 --> 00:27:54,737
the cultural center

676
00:27:54,772 --> 00:27:56,481
of the city of Pripyat.

677
00:27:56,482 --> 00:27:57,798
And indeed, this was a place

678
00:27:57,833 --> 00:27:59,115
where friends gathered,

679
00:27:59,116 --> 00:28:01,290
where there would be

680
00:28:01,325 --> 00:28:02,491
celebrations,

681
00:28:02,492 --> 00:28:03,858
there would be balls,

682
00:28:03,893 --> 00:28:05,225
there would be music,

683
00:28:05,226 --> 00:28:06,958
there would be dancing,

684
00:28:06,959 --> 00:28:10,234
there would be performing

685
00:28:10,269 --> 00:28:13,509
on the stage here behind me.

686
00:28:13,544 --> 00:28:15,742
But after 20 years,

687
00:28:15,743 --> 00:28:17,044
the forces of nature

688
00:28:17,046 --> 00:28:17,977
have started to decay

689
00:28:18,012 --> 00:28:21,522
this facility.

690
00:28:21,523 --> 00:28:23,325
This concrete soviet facade

691
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,458
may look imposing

692
00:28:25,459 --> 00:28:26,160
but it's no match

693
00:28:26,161 --> 00:28:29,465
for the frigid ukranian winters.

694
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:30,397
As the temperature drops

695
00:28:30,398 --> 00:28:31,869
below freezing,

696
00:28:31,870 --> 00:28:33,102
water that has accumulated

697
00:28:33,137 --> 00:28:35,270
in cracks, expands,

698
00:28:35,305 --> 00:28:36,676
exerting bursting pressure

699
00:28:36,678 --> 00:28:38,079
that pulls apart

700
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,419
the masonry.

701
00:28:40,454 --> 00:28:42,657
As vegetation grows unchecked,

702
00:28:42,692 --> 00:28:43,417
the roots spread

703
00:28:43,418 --> 00:28:46,492
through foundations and stairs.

704
00:28:46,494 --> 00:28:49,248
These roots suck in moisture

705
00:28:49,283 --> 00:28:52,002
that makes them expand and grow.

706
00:28:52,003 --> 00:28:54,637
Like miniature hydraulic jacks,

707
00:28:54,672 --> 00:28:55,538
over time,

708
00:28:55,539 --> 00:28:57,312
they slowly push apart

709
00:28:57,347 --> 00:29:03,156
the concrete.

710
00:29:03,191 --> 00:29:06,396
This is only 20 years.

711
00:29:06,397 --> 00:29:07,227
Can you imagine

712
00:29:07,262 --> 00:29:08,058
what this facility

713
00:29:08,059 --> 00:29:16,542
will look like after 200 years?

714
00:29:16,543 --> 00:29:17,779
After the accident,

715
00:29:17,814 --> 00:29:19,616
scientists expected the worst

716
00:29:19,617 --> 00:29:22,281
for the wildlife in the region.

717
00:29:22,282 --> 00:29:23,083
Most of the trees

718
00:29:23,084 --> 00:29:24,871
in a 11/2 square mile area

719
00:29:24,906 --> 00:29:26,659
around the nuclear plant

720
00:29:26,660 --> 00:29:29,564
were killed off by radiation.

721
00:29:29,599 --> 00:29:32,999
Many animals died.

722
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,852
But incredibly, the effect

723
00:29:34,887 --> 00:29:36,705
of the absence of humans

724
00:29:36,706 --> 00:29:39,180
for 20 years has outweighed

725
00:29:39,215 --> 00:29:40,251
the initial damage

726
00:29:40,252 --> 00:29:47,593
Caused by the nuclear nightmare.

727
00:29:47,628 --> 00:29:49,266
this is the red forest,

728
00:29:49,301 --> 00:29:50,127
an area

729
00:29:50,128 --> 00:29:51,570
that was horribly impacted

730
00:29:51,605 --> 00:29:54,239
by radioactivity

